HOST - Sets the target host and port
QUIT - Exits the Back Orifice client
PINGLIST - Pings a lits of ip addresses in a text file
SWEEP - Sweeps a subnet with ping packets
SWEEPLIST - Sweeps a list of subnets in a text file
PASSWD - Sets the encryption password for client
DIR - Display remote files with wildcards
note:  If filespec is not provided, a list of the current remote directory is provided
GET - Transfers a file from remote host to the local computer
note:  If localfilename is not provided file is stored in current local directory
PUT - Transfers a file from local computer to the remote host
note:  If remotefilename is not provided file is stored in current remote directory
FIND - Search a directory tree for filespec
REN - Renames a file or directory
example:  dialog "Get back to work you lazy bum!" "A message from the management:"
note:  Use 'keylog stop' to end keyboard logging
NETVIEW - Display resources available on the network
NETCONNECT - Connect to a network resource
NETDISCONNECT - Disconnects from a network resource
NETLIST - List current incomming and outgoing network connections
RESOLVE - Resolves the ip of a hostname from the remote host
note:  processid's are listed by PROCLIST
example:  procspawn command.com /C netstat -na > c:\windows	emp
LISTCAPS - Lists the video capture devices
CAPSCREEN - Captures an image of the current screen to a bitmap
CAPFRAME - Captures a frame from a video capture device to a bitmap
note:  If all or part of or part of the device info is not provided default is 0,640,480,16
CAPAVI - Captures video from a video capture device to an AVI
note:  If all or part of or part of the device info is not provided default is 0,320,240,16
REDIRLIST - Lists the current port redirections
note:  If no output port is provided the input port is used.
APPADD - Spawns a console application on a tcp port
APPDEL - Removes a console application from the redirected console apps
REGMAKEKEY - Creates a key in the registry
REGDELKEY - Deletes a key from the registry
REGLISTKEYS - Lists the subkeys of a key
REGLISTVALS - Lists the values of a key
REGDELVAL - Deletes a value from a key
REGSETVAL - Sets the value of a key, creating it if it did not already exist
example3: regsetval HLEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\StringValue "S,This is a string value"
note:  Binary values (type B) are specified in two digit hex values, Dword values (type D) in decimal
note:  If no root is supplied, all drives are accessable via http
TCPSEND - Connects the server to an ip and sends a file
TCPRECV - Connects the server to an ip and receives a file
LOCKUP - Locks up the remote machine
PLUGINKILL - Tells a plugin to terminate
